<TITLE> Biman becomes PLC with new name by June </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 20 (bdnews24.com)  The loss-making Biman Bangladesh Airlines is converting to a public limited company by the end of June. The national flag carrier will start from the scratch with a new name, Bangladesh Airlines Ltd, civil aviation adviser MA Matin told reporters Wednesday after an inter-ministerial meeting. He said the government will take liabilities of all debts of the sinking airliner is buckling under . Matin said the government will float an international tender to appoint a foreign operator to run the airlines. The new operator will take steps necessary to pull Biman back into profits. Biman has Tk 2,000 crore in loans, including a whopping Tk 1,600 crore to Bangladesh Petroleum Corporation that supplies fuel. The adviser said 49 percent of the company's shares would be offered to the public and the government would retain the remainder. To make Biman a pubic limited company, laws have been amended, which be placed at the cabinet meeting for approval Saturday. Some 1,600 employees of the state-run airlines have applied for 'golden handshakes' in an expression of their desire to go into voluntary retirement responding to a government proposal in line with current plans to corporatise it. Adviser Matin told reporters: "Currently the number of employees stands at 4,800. The number will be reduced to 3,400." bdnews24.c
